 </svg>Airline Regulations</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3">According to <a href="https://www.iata.org/en/programs/cargo/dgr/lithium-batteries/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandOrange hover:underline">IATA regulations</a>, passengers may carry power banks up to 100Wh without airline approval. For 100-160Wh, airline approval is required. Anything above 160Wh is prohibited for passenger flights.</p>
