 <!-- Section 9: GB47372-2026 -->
 <section id="gb47372" class="mb-16">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">9. What Is the GB47372-2026 New Power Bank Standard?</h2>

 <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-4 rounded-r-lg border border-slate-200 mb-6">
 <p class="text-[11px] font-black text-brandOrange uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Quick answer</p>
 <p class="text-slate-700 leading-relaxed text-sm">GB47372-2026 is China's new mandatory power bank standard. Published March 2026, enforceable April 2027. It tightens cell quality, protection circuit requirements, and adds enhanced UN38.3 transport tests. Industry estimates suggest ~70% of low-end Chinese capacity will be eliminated. WOWOHCOOL is already GB47372-ready.</p>
 </div>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">For B2B buyers sourcing from China, GB47372-2026 is the most consequential regulatory event of the cycle. The standard does three things at once: (1) raises the cell quality floor by mandating tighter capacity and cycle-life conformance, (2) tightens protection circuit requirements covering over-current, over-voltage, over-temperature, and short-circuit protection, and (3) layers enhanced UN38.3 transport tests on top of existing requirements. The full standard text is published on the <a href="https://std.samr.gov.cn/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue font-bold underline">China National Public Service Platform for Standards Information</a>.</p>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic mb-4">Timeline at a Glance</h3>
 <div class="overflow-x-auto bg-white rounded-lg border border-slate-200 mb-6">
 <table class="w-full">
 <thead class="bg-slate-100">
 <tr>
 <th class="text-left p-4 font-black text-slate-900 uppercase text-sm">Phase</th>
 <th class="text-left p-4 font-black text-slate-900 uppercase text-sm">Date</th>
 <th class="text-left p-4 font-black text-slate-900 uppercase text-sm">What it means for buyers</th>
 </tr>
 </thead>
 <tbody>
 <tr class="border-t border-slate-200">
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600 font-bold">Standard published</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">March 2026</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Specs locked in. Compliant factories begin re-tooling.</td>
 </tr>
 <tr class="border-t border-slate-200">
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600 font-bold">Voluntary compliance window</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">2026 to Q1 2027</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Buyers can request GB47372-ready batches at no premium.</td>
 </tr>
 <tr class="border-t border-slate-200 bg-brandOrange/5">
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600 font-bold">Mandatory enforcement</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-brandOrange font-semibold">April 2027</td>
 <td class="p-4 text-slate-600">Non-compliant production cannot be exported. ~70% of low-end Chinese capacity is forecast to exit.</td>
 </tr>
 </tbody>
 </table>
 </div>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic mb-4">What This Means for Your 2026-2027 Sourcing Plan</h3>
 <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-600 text-sm mb-6">
 <li><strong>Audit your current supplier now.</strong> Ask them in writing whether they are GB47372-2026 ready. If they cannot answer or stall, plan a switch before Q4 2026.</li>
 <li><strong>Lock GB47372-ready capacity early.</strong> As enforcement approaches, ready capacity gets tight. WOWOHCOOL is already certified-ready and accepting Q3-Q4 2026 bookings.</li>
 <li><strong>Use the compliance window as a marketing edge.</strong> Tell your retail partners your power banks are pre-compliant with the 2027 Chinese standard, even before the deadline. It signals quality leadership.</li>
 <li><strong>Re-verify cell suppliers.</strong> Many low-tier cell suppliers will not survive the standard. Confirm your factory's cell BOM uses tier-1 suppliers (CATL, ATL, EVE, Lishen).</li>
 </ul>

